import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.geojson")

    # Group data by state and count airports
    state_counts = data.groupby("state").size().reset_index(name="count")

    # Merge state_counts with us_states
    us_states = us_states.merge(state_counts, left_on="name", right_on="state")

    # Create a GeoDataFrame
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(us_states, geometry="geometry")

    # Plot the choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(12, 6))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    gdf.plot(column="count", cmap="coolwarm", linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor="0.8", legend=True, cax=cax)

    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports by state?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Count the number of airports per country
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts().reset_index()
    country_counts.columns = ['country', 'count']

    # Create a bar chart of the number of airports per country
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='country', y='count', data=country_counts)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Country', ylabel='Number of Airports')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of distances between airports and the reference point?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Distance")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='state', palette='viridis', legend='brief')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude coordinates of airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=800, height=800).generate(text)

    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
